<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO ARTHUR'S POSTS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Aug  7 13:25:35 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Arthur- I am considering what you said, and you have made several points that i agree with and am guilty of.  Of course I flamed, roared, stuped to a new low, whatever. I am human, afterall, like Ed (alas). I just let my frustration overwhelm my common sense more than it should.<br><br>
I will process, calmly, your input. Sure Richard can talk for himself when he chooses. I just got involved because I saw this global sense of change happening to this site, and to me it was a cheapening (my opinion), and I choose (perhaps a control need - but I don't think so) to stand up to this new tide of name calling. As a result I got sucked into the rip tide and became just like them. <br><br>
I am not playing both sides, I read, think, try and understand, absorb, and sometimes change my point of view when I am educated to a better postion.  The example that comes to mind is the use of the word &quot;gook&quot;. Two months ago there was an outcry about someone using it, from many of the regulars. Now, when Cook or Ed use it, no one says a word. That silence scares me. I guess I overreact because it seems no one else is.  I will stop now, I want to re read your input.<br><br>
If you wish to think of me playing mental games, I can't help that. But please, I am just another guy, another bozo on this bus, for better or worse, I just tend to be more outspoken, I guess, for my own good.
